            <formatted-text>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='12'>KEY INSIGHTS</run>
              <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontsize='8'>📉 The Sensex declined from 81,287 to 71,948 (-11.49%) during the peak market stress period, reflecting a significant loss in investor confidence.</run>
              <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontsize='8'>📈 India VIX surged from 13.70 to 27.89 (+103.58%), indicating a sharp increase in market volatility and fear following the Strait of Hormuz disruption.</run>
              <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontsize='8'>⚠️ The crisis period clearly demonstrates an inverse relationship between market volatility and equity performance, with rising uncertainty driving stock prices lower.</run>
              <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontsize='8'>📊 Although the Sensex recovered partially after April 2026, India VIX gradually declined, suggesting that investor confidence improved as geopolitical uncertainty eased.</run>
            </formatted-text>
